Former Nasarawa State Governor, Senator Abdullahi Adamu has emerged the new National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress, APC. DAILY POST reports that he emerged through a consensus arrangement after other aspirants withdrew from the race. Also elected through consensus is Emma Enukwu from Enugu State as the Deputy National Chairman, South. The consensus candidates were confirmed through voice vote at the ongoing national convention of the party. As of the time of filing this report, more officials of the party who also emerged unopposed are being announced. More to comeâ€¦